values:
So...I totally just cut 14 inches off my hair.  It is so short now...but really cute.  I'm gonna be donating the beautiful hair to Locks of Love.  

Drea, I can't believe you're going to be home soon!  Fun times to be had I'm sure!

You Are 72% Lady
Overall, you are a refined lady with excellent manners. But you also know when to relax and not get too serious about etiquette
Are You A Lady?

So...on Wednesday morning my boss informed all of us that she is retiring on March 31st. So, that means that I will work harder than ever to get a different job. I will not be at the library without her and this will give me the nudge I need to find a different job.  I was hesitant because I love the library, but now I can leave in peace.

I'm really sad about all of this and could use some time to get over it.  I adore my boss and working at the library, but now I can move on and feel really great about it.

I hope you all had a great Thanksgivin
Yay!  Democrats now rule!  Woot Woot!!

Just wanted to let y'all know that the journal arrived here safely today.  I haven't had it since March!  Wow!  I made posts in Vegas, but they were Vegas related.

I may keep it hostage for awhile.

MWAHAHAHA!
Just wanted to remind those of you close to Galena that my fall concert is October 14th at 7:30 and October 15th at 3:00.  I really hope those who can will try to make it.

So...I didn't get the job at the ARC.  Shoulda known that would happen.  I'm used to the rejection, but since they only interviewed one other person besides me I'm taking it especially hard.  I had a 50% chance of getting the job and still didn't get it.  I feel really great about myself right now.

Also, I'm upset for my bro because he worked really hard at being prepared for the fall play audition and he didn't get a part.  I'm really fucking sick of "I'm a bastard named Ron Jenkins" being so damned political about everything.  Granted it is only a three person cast, but he cast someone who I can't understand a word he is saying onstage but because he's the damn president or vice-president or something he gets the freakin' part!  He always did this to me too, and I'm so sick of his "visions" of the way the cast should be!  It's sickening that you have to be one of his "henchmen" or an "officer" to get a part at all.  So Nick is forced to be Student Director which is just a glorified term for the gofer of the whole mother fucking play!  You can mess with me but don't mess with my brother!  I'm really tempted to give that prick a piece of my mind.

***okay, rant over...moving on...deep breath in, slowly let it out***

So...I could use some encouragement right now.  Because I was sick last week I didn't go to therapy and now I can't get my therapist to return my phone calls so I can't get a new appointment.  AHHHH! I need someone to bitch and complain to.  I'm going crazy!!!!  I'm seriously having major breakdowns about things.  I was almost crying because I was so upset for my brother.  I can't stand that good people always get the shaft, and now Sara won't be able to see my brother on stage yet again.  Mother Fucker!!!

So...I'm awaiting word on a job I applied for.  I interviewed yesterday and I am supposed to receive word on it by today already.  I'm excited for it, but saddened also.  I can probably stay at the library (according to the lady who interviewed me,) but I don't know what I want anymore.  The job is at the ARC here in Galena, and I would be the Preschool assistant and working with the Kids Club after school.  It sounds really lovely...but moving on is hard.  Keep me in your thoughts on that one.

Otherwise, everything is fine.  I've nothing new to report at this time.  I am feeling a little better, and hope to stay that way.

Love and miss all of you.  I haven't really seen Teresa or Sara for awhile.  Damn election and Cuba City livin'!

Yeah...so I'm sick...got the flu or something in the form of a massive case of diarrhea.  I know, I know, TMI, but I'm allowed to ramble.  It is 3:00 in the morning and I'm not sleeping.  I have to "go" every ten seconds (almost not an exaggeration) and my bum is sore now.  I'm supposed to work in the morning, but if this doesn't clear up that isn't going to happen...and I'm filling in for someone who is sick!  The damn library is falling apart at the seams!

Oh, and my wonderful church gave me $200 out of the discretionary fund for my doctor bill.  I love my church family!

>2. WERE YOU NAMED AFTER ANYONE? Yes
>3. WHEN DID YOU LAST CRY? tonight because I'm sick and I just want to go to sleep but can't 'cuz I have diarrhea
 4. DO YOU LIKE YOUR HANDWRITING? yes
 5. WHAT IS YOUR FAVORITE LUNCHMEAT? honey ham
>>6. KIDS? I hope I'm blessed someday
>> 7. IF YOU WERE ANOTHER PERSON WOULD YOU BE FRIENDS WITH YOU? uhhh...I hope so
>8. DO YOU HAVE A JOURNAL?  the traveling journal and livejournal and an occasional "real" journal that I am terrible about updating.
>9. DO YOU USE SARCASM A LOT? yes
>> 10. DO YOU STILL HAVE YOUR TONSILS? nope
>>11. WOULD YOU BUNGEE JUMP? never in a million years
>12. WHAT IS YOUR FAVORITE CEREAL? fruity pebbles
>>13. DO YOU UNTIE YOUR SHOES WHEN YOU TAKE THEM OFF? not usually

>15. WHAT IS YOUR FAVORITE ICE CREAM FLAVOR? Mint chocolate cookie from Ben & Jerry
>> 16. WHAT SIZE SHOE? 9

>18. WHAT IS THE LEAST FAVORITE THING ABOUT YOURSELF? my body definitely

>>20. DO YOU WANT EVERYONE TO SEND THIS BACK TO YOU? only if they want.
>21. WHAT COLOR PANTS AND SHOES ARE YOU WEARING? white capris and no shoes (it should be bedtime)

 23. WHAT ARE YOU LISTENING TO RIGHT NOW? sounds of the night and the fan

>> 26. WHO WAS THE LAST PERSON YOU TALKED TO ON THE PHONE? tough one...I think Mike on Saturday night
>27. THE FIRST THING YOU NOTICE ABOUT PEOPLE YOU ARE ATTRACTED TO? ass, eyes, personality
>28. DO YOU LIKE THE PERSON WHO SENT THIS TO YOU? hells yes, I love my T!
>29. FAVORITE DRINK? diet coke, black cherry fresca, and tea
>30. FAVORITE SPORT? Baseball
>31. EYE COLOR? brown
>32. HAT SIZE? uhh...hats have sizes? M/L? is that hat size?
>33. DO YOU WEAR CONTACTS? yes, and I just got my prescription renewed so I have them again!

>35. SCARY MOVIES OR HAPPY ENDINGS? happy ending...but usually I like when everything doesn't end up all perfect.

>48. THE FURTHEST YOU'VE BEEN FROM HOME? Scotland and England

Mariel,
My bro and 'rents are coming down to visit DuPaul on Tuesday!  Nick is thinking of applying.

Oh and by the way...my ER visit before I left on vacation is going to cost me.....drumroll please....$890!

Fuck me

'nuff said

So...hello livejournal world.  How are you?  It seems that I haven't posted in a long time...but other people haven't posted either.

The trip was fun.  We had a great time, even though it was bastardly hot out there.  It did make the weather here seem like nothing however, so some good came of it.

I feel crappy right now.  Every time I eat I get really bad stomach pains and I'm thinking maybe an ulcer?  I'm dying?  Food betraying me?  Any thoughts from my lj pals out there???

So, my stomach hurts so bad that I don't eat, and then I feel kinda weak all day because I don't eat.  But the alternative is extreme stomach pain and feeling like I'm gonna barf all the time.  

AHHHHHHH!!!

Anyway, hope to see my wayward friends soon.

So...I had a fun day yesterday.  Had a little stint in the ER.  Two vials of blood, a bolles of saline, and a script for painkillers later, they still don't know what's wrong with me.  Able to go to Vegas, but I am still in pain.  Ugh!

Just wanted to thank Andrea for my now sour mood...want to thank most of my friends for disappointing me...want to just crawl under a rock and cry for awhile...love it when my friends back out of commitments...can't even imagine just throwing money away like that...sound really bitchy and negative but I don't care right now...wow, so glad that I get to see my friends...on our FRIENDS NO MATTER WHAT vacation, when the two people furthest away aren't coming...so glad that while I want to be excited for being able to spend time with T, Sara and Travis I can't be excited because I'm so upset and depleted and pissed off frankly...just want to...go...and....

So...the staged reading Sara and I are doing is the weekend.  Saturday at 7:30 (Teresa, you're still coming then right?) and Sunday at 3:00.  It has been fun, but I'll be glad when it is over.  I can't believe we leave for our trip in less than a month!  Mandy, get ready for some wild phone calls when we are there!  Let us know when you will be home and we'll call you lots so that it feels like you are there!

Teresa, Sara and I desperately want to get out for some fun sometime this week, so if you do go to the show on Saturday we would really like to maybe do something afterwards.  Maybe a late dinner or ice cream or something.

The show is really cute, and I think everyone who comes will enjoy it.  

I miss those of you who I haven't seen in awhile.  I wish you all well.

So...last night was the library sleepover for the summer reading program.  It was interesting to say the least.  We had about thirty kids here and two to three teen advisors and me here at a time.  The kids were really wild, but we still had fun.  It took them forever to fall asleep, and I ended up not spending the night because every single child slept upstairs, and it was just too noisy for me (I really need to get over this soon.)  I left about 12:30 or so and Cody was here over-seeing the few kids that weren't yet totally asleep and then he too was going to go home.  Alison, Aubreigh and Janet all fell asleep almost immediately and so it left just me to watch all of the kids.  I probably made something like 100 trips up and down the stairs last night with various children and stuff, so today it feels like I ran a marathon or something.  I am really exhausted even though I slept until almost 9:30.  I didn't go to sleep right away when I got home, because I was very wound up.

Anywho, the kids had a great time and we didn't have any get homesick (except one who was only here for twenty minutes.)  It was a huge success!

You Passed the US Citizenship Test
Congratulations - you got 10 out of 10 correct!
Could You Pass the US Citizenship Test?

Slow and Steady
Your friends see you as painstaking and fussy. They see you as very cautious, extremely careful, a slow and steady plodder. It'd really surprise them if you ever did something impulsively or on the spur of the moment. They expect you to examine everything carefully from every angle and then usually decide against it.
How Do People See You?

You Belong in 1973
If you scored... 1950 - 1959: You're fun loving, romantic, and more than a little innocent. See you at the drive in! 1960 - 1969: You are a free spirit with a huge heart. Love, peace, and happiness rule - oh, and drugs too. 1970 - 1979: Bold and brash, you take life by the horns. Whether you're partying or protesting, you give it your all! 1980 - 1989: Wild, over the top, and just a little bit cheesy. You're colorful at night - and successful during the day. 1990 - 1999: With you anything goes! You're grunge one day, ghetto fabulous the next. It's all good!
What Year Do You Belong In?

Your Inner Child Is Angry
You're not an angry person. But when you don't get your way, watch out. Like a very manipulative kid, you will get what you want. Even if it takes a little kicking and screaming.
How Is Your Inner Child?

Teresa and Sara,
The airfare is steadily going up!  I think we need to purchase as soon as possible!  Originally each flight was $129, and now they went up by $30 for each flight!  Ahhhh!!!  We need to check daily now or we may end up paying a lot more than we can afford!!!

So...my wonderful, fantastic, awesome granny agreed to give me $500 for our trip!!!  Yay!!!  I'll have to pay it back of course, but I won't have to bust my ass trying to fund the trip all at once! I can pay her back in installments instead!!  I figure I will only have to come up with a couple hundred more to really have my bases covered.  I figure airfare/condo will cost about $385 and then maybe $300-$400 for spending money.  I won't to make sure I have enough in case something happens.

My job is driving me nuts right now...mainly because I'm not there enough and they are giving me enough work to last several weeks,a dn I just won't get to a lot of it until...well, I'm not sure I will get to it!  Ivo (my dad's boss) says he may have a job for me to do until I can get something more permanent!  That would be fantastic!  I know he needs helps getting products priced, so that should keep me busy for awhile.

I agreed to take Makayla tomorrow without thinking that I have therapy smack dab in the middle of my time with her.  I missed last week because Cathy was sick, and I could cancel this week but I'm going to see if she has anything else open.  I am sometimes such an airhead...and then other times I'm the only one on top of things.  Ay, ay, ay...

Teresa, I will be done covering lunches at 1:30 on Friday, so if you want to do stuff, great.  Sara isn't able to purchase tickets with us this weekend because she is going to Grinnell, but maybe we can order them for her and she can have the money there for us.  I have to cater Saturday night, but Friday I am free after 1:30 (as I stated already.)

Can't wait to see you all next week.  Are we planning something on Friday? Sunday? Monday?  My days are filling up, so please, let's try to get some definitives laid out.

So, until this play is over I will not be working very much at all...unless someone is sick or needs time off or something.  It kinda stinks because I do not have enough time to get all of my work done, and while they want to be able to give me more hours, they claim it "isn't in the budget" so I guess that is just how it will be.  

I'm going to apply for a couple more jobs today (secretarial, since the hours are ideal) and then see where that gets me.  

Nothing new going on here really, but the weather is starting to upset me, mainly because of all the rain.  We have a party planned for my father on Saturday, rather our friends the Feece's do, and we are hoping it isn't going to rain because they planned for it to happen outside.  They are throwing him a party in honor of his new job and whatnot.  I'm excited; it should be fun.

Well, gotta go write a cover letter (if I can remember how to do one) and get my resume off.

Ciao

So, I saw Sara's apartment tonight!  I'm so happy for her, and even happier knowing that I can visit a lot!  Yay for her!

Nothing new here.  Just looking forward to living vicariously through my brother on Saturday when he has prom.  I remember it as being such a great night.  My father's last day at the "cheese prison" as he calls it is tomorrow, and then he will start for Ivo very soon.  For those of you who don't know, my dad is working for Chef Ivo who is opening a shop downtown.  My dad is very excited and the shop will be open in a couple of weeks. 

I can't wait to see you all very soon.

Ciao

Teresa,
Just a question...will we go from the 16th to the 21st?  I just want to know so that I can put in for my vacation.  Also, we need to keep an eye on the tickets so they don't sell out on us.  Also, how is Andrea/Tony going to get there?

Love you all lots!

Just wanted to tell y'all that I got a part in "I Remember Mama," which my church is doing in June.  It is a staged reading which means that we are able to use our scripts onstage, but otherwise it is just like a real performance.  Sara tried out as well, and I am sure that she got a part.  I'm just not sure which one she got.

Otherwise, nothing else is new with me.

Can't wait to see you all.

(Vegas baby, Vegas!)

I'm in so much pain!!!!  I'm having terrible back spasms and no matter what I try to do they keep coming.  I really don't want to pay the money to see someone.  I'm in agony!!!!

Anywho, that was all I wanted to say.  I miss you all loads and hope to see you soon.

I've been checking out places online also, and there are some great deals for May/June, but none posted for July yet.  I just found out I have to house/dog sit July 7th-9th, so let's stay away from those dates.

Teresa, are you having any luck yet?

It was so beautiful today; I spent a good chunk of the afternoon outside at Ruth and Darrell Feece's house with my doggies and their doggies.  They are the ones I will be house-sitting for.

Nothing new in my life, as usual.

I miss those of you who are wayward!

VEGAS BABY, VEGAS!!!

I want to go RIGHT NOW!!!  I can't wait!  We have a definite agenda when we get there, and you all know what this is....  Let's keep it on the down low though!

Anyone up to going to Dubuque this evening?

Wow....they did such a wonderful job!  I'm actually looking forward to seeing it twice more!  Ron definitely picked the right Marian!  She was so good.  The only downfall was that the singing was fantastic, but they pulled it off!

Yay to GHS and the "little ones" in it as well!

Teresa,
My boss is having me over to dinner one of the nights of the play and then we are going to go to the play, so I will have to get back to you.
I'm at work...and bored out of my mind because all I can think about is eating.  I get to eat as soon as Janet is done, but I can't last much longer...food...I need food...

It is raining here...which makes for a very dreary day.  I keep thinking that soon it will be April, and April is when Sara gets back!!  Yay!!!

Not much else is going on with me at the moment.  I'm trying to stay ahead of my brother's schedule for the next two weeks.  He has got baseball games most every night and the musical opens next week.  Whew, the poor kid is running around like crazy.

I'm looking forward to seeing the musical, and I hope it comes together soon because my brother is worried that it won't.

Girls...I am planning on sending the journal out to Teresa today...so she should get it soon.

Oh...and T, my bro's play is April 6th, 7th, and 8th.  Would you like to go sometime...with me?  Yeah, um just let me know and we can make plans.  

I have to agree with Sara...Memorial Day seems really far away.  I'm not sure what I'm doing yet, but will tentatively plan on being there for whatever you all plan.  


I can't wait to see you Sara!  And Drea! and to spend time with Ruth! and T and Mandy too!  

Hooray for friends!

I love you all.

Okay all...I went to the doctor today and I have an ear infection to start with.  Otherwise, he has no rhyme or reason as to why I have fainting spells.  He checked all the necessary stuff, ie: heart rate, blood pressure, my thyroid and signs of diabetes, and they are all normal.  His best guess is that I am just unlucky, and some factors that most people tolerate, like extreme temperature, getting up from a sitting/laying position, are hard for me to handle.  He said that fainting at my age is perfectly normal and not to worry about it.  He could do a blood work-up, but since I don't have insurance it would be really expensive and 99% of the time it comes back normal anyway.  

So...the long and short of it is that it could happen again really soon, in years to come, or never again.  

That's all I have to say.

Yay...so I passed out again on Saturday.  This time at choir practice.  My surrogate grandparents freaked out over that.  Now they want me to spend mega bucks on seeing a doctor...some even agreed to pay for it.  HMMMMM...maybe I'll take them up on that.

Everything else is fine...my St. Pat's day was very boring.

I was really counting on snow today...damn weathermen being wrong.  We were supposed to be drowning in snow by now, and all I've seen is a few flurries here and there.  When I watched the weather this morning the meteorologists were trying to cover their asses by saying the storm blew north and now we MIGHT see some snowfall.  I don't, however, think we are going to get 6-8" like they originally predicted.

OH, and I am almost done with the journal and will be sending it on to Teresa soon.  

Love and miss all of you.

Yeah, so I went with Meta to see Gaelic Storm at the Irish Cottage last night!!  It was so awesome, and I'd never heard them before.  It was really crowded though and people were really drunk, but we had a good time.  My ear is still pounding today from the noise, but I have been having problems with it for awhile so I think it is just in shock.  

Anywho, I wrote more about the concert in the journal (thanks for sending it Drea) and I will write more schtuff in it soon.

Love and miss you all!!

I had forgotten that yesterday would have been Becky's 24th birthday.  Maybe I didn't forget but instead pretended that I did so that the pain wouldn't be there.  I was kind of "off" yesterday, and now I realize why.  

It is still so very intangible to me...her death, the fact that I won't see her again, and my question of "Where is she?"  I'm not really sure where she is right now.  I'm a big believer in heaven and hell, and it frightens me to think that she would be in hell.  I want to go against what I've been taught; that people who commit suicide are condemned to hell.  I want to believe that she is in heaven having one hell of a good time and that God has put her to work cleaning up the joint.  It makes me feel better to think that she is in heaven and not hell.  I don't want anyone I care so much about to be in hell.  However, my version of "hell" isn't really that bad of a place.  I think she may actually be more in purgatory and that she is very contemplative about her life.  I am somewhat happier thinking these thoughts instead of the alternative.

I think I will go visit her grave tomorrow when I am out and about.  I periodically go up there to visit her and my grandfather since they are neighbors in the cemetery.  

I'm especially thinking of my girls during this time and we have gotten through almost five months so far and it will get easier, for that I am sure.

It has been nice at work this week...mainly because I have been able to work a lot but also because Maren has been sick all week.  I hope she feels better soon, but it makes me happy because I don't have to do much!!

So...Sara I talked to your mom at Dick's yesterday and she said you weren't coming home until the 12th of April.  You make it any longer and I'm going to have to come over there and get you!! (j/k by the way, but hurry back dammit!)

Nothing new to report.

Gotta go and work...ha ha ha, yeah right!
The computer seems to be moving...I am so dizzy I can hardly read what I am writing.  That probably isn't a good thing is it.  OH....must stop the movement....help me....

The Vagina Monologues fucking rocked!!!  And the best part was that I saw it with three women who are either pushing sixty or are sixty and we had a fantastic time.  It was so awesome!  They had a sold out crowd, which was so great for them.  It was odd on the way home when we were talking about the show, because we got into a conversations about the "c" word (which I never use) and is the subject of a monologue in the show called, "Reclaiming Cunt."  It was very weird to talk about that with my library co-workers!

Anywho, twas very cool to see it and the acting was so great.

In some way I feel better that Justin wasn't murdered.  It is just too weird to me.  I don't want someone I went to school with or know really well to be murdered.  However, I don't like that it was related to drugs (he got a hold of bad drugs just to update Sara and Drea.)
